
[1]hellebore

   HEL'LEBORE, n. [L. helleborus.] The name of several plants of different
   genera, the most important of which are the black hellebore, Christmas
   rose, or Christmas flower, of the genus Helleborus, and the white
   hellebore, of the genus Veratrum. Both are acrid and poisonous,and are
   used in medicine as evacuants and alternatives.
